modules.description: Handles event lifecycle callbacks for status updates, low-priority alerts, and critical failures. Accepts functions to execute when specific event states are triggered. Used to integrate real-time monitoring and alerting into system workflows.

Provides functions to retrieve battery level and charging status, with callbacks for real-time updates. Operates on numeric values representing percentage and boolean flags indicating charge state. Used to implement power-aware features in mobile applications.

Manages real-time status updates, low-priority alerts, and critical failures through event-driven callbacks. It supports custom functions for handling specific states, enabling dynamic system responses. Key operations include registering callback handlers and triggering actions based on event severity. For example, it can log low-battery warnings or initiate shutdown procedures on critical failures.
